	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok, I'm only an 18th level, very new (started December 2000) wizard, so don't flame me for being inexperienced, but here are my opinions.<BR>
<BR>
I love playing a wizard. That's all that matters. I also have a few tanks: a level 6 warrior and a level 5 monk. I ABHOR those characters because all I have to do is click the autoattack button and go grab a snack while either my HP or the mob's HP go down.<BR>
<BR>
I don't play a wizard because I can duel other characters, I play to have fun with other characters by grouping with them. I've only played two duels: one was in a guild tourney, and the other was because a 7th level warrior, for some reason, accepted my challenge (made only as a joke). I play a wizard because I love the combination of strategy (especially when soloing), group involvement (raids), and sheer, unmatched magical firepower (don't start flaming me; I do believe wizards are the best nukers).<BR>
<BR>
I don't like playing warriors because playing them often involves little more than clicking autoattack and grabbing a snack in RL while my character whacks away with a sword. I don't play pet summoners (though I've thought of trying magician) for almost the same reason. I don't play bards because...well...I just don't like the concept of bards :). Finally, I don't play chanters or clerics because I like to see the effect of my attacks on a mob, even if the special effects aren't that great.<BR>
<BR>
So, to settle this matter on mage vs. wizard vs. necro vs. shaman vs. bard, WHO CARES? If you're this competitive, go play multiplayer Diablo or something where you CAN duke it out w/o fear of losing XP. This game is about working together (a chief reason I play it). Everyone needs everybody else. If you want to solo, go ahead, but you won't survive higher levels (from what I've heard).<BR>
<BR>
And to anyone who said wizards suck @$$ and &lt;insert class here&gt; rules without giving any reason, I hope a wizard abandons you on an evil plane and refuses to TP you back to retrieve your rotting corpse &gt;:-(
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
